--- !u!114 &1008417462
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1008417461}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 92c69c561b7cbf2429a04d41c4feac25, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  _30pointQ:
  - questionInfo: "What does \u201Cpharmacokinetics\u201D include?"
    questionChoices:
    - Pharmacological effects of drugs.
    - Unwanted effects of drugs.
    - Chemical structure of a medicinal agent.
    - Distribution of drugs in the organism.
    correctChoice: Distribution of drugs in the organism.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The main mechanism of most drugs absorption in GI tract is:'
    questionChoices:
    - Active transport (carrier-mediated diffusion).
    - Filtration (aqueous diffusion).
    - Endocytosis and exocytosis.
    - Passive diffusion (lipid diffusion).
    correctChoice: Passive diffusion (lipid diffusion).
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "What does the term \u201Cbioavailability\u201D mean?"
    questionChoices:
    - Plasma protein binding degree of substance.
    - Permeability through the brain-blood barrier.
    - Fraction of an uncharged drug reaching the systemic circulation following any
      route administration.
    - Amount of a substance in urine relative to the initial doze.
    correctChoice: Fraction of an uncharged drug reaching the systemic circulation
      following any route administration.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Who is the scientist that give the term hormone to the chemicals
      secreted from endocrine  glands?
    questionChoices:
    - Starling.
    - Frank.
    - Guyton.
    - Ganong.
    correctChoice: Starling.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Where is the cardiac pacemaker located?
    questionChoices:
    - Left ventricle.
    - Right ventricle.
    - Right atrium.
    - Left atrium.
    correctChoice: Right atrium.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The cells that work as a gastrointestinal system pacemaker is?
    questionChoices:
    - Cells of Cajal.
    - Cells of Langerhans.
    - Bitz cell.
    - "Peyer\u2019s cells."
    correctChoice: Cells of Cajal.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: If the heart rate is 100/minutes what is the time of one cardiac
      cycle?
    questionChoices:
    - 0.8 seconds.
    - 1.0 second.
    - 1.2 seconds.
    - 0.6 seconds.
    correctChoice: 1.2 seconds.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: What the respiratory rate if inhalation take 1.2 second and Exhalation
      takes 1.8 second?
    questionChoices:
    - 12 breaths per minute
    - 15 breaths per minute
    - 25 breaths per minute
    - 33 breaths per minute
    correctChoice: 33 breaths per minute
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following is the most likely cause for black discoloration
      of the bronchial lymph nodes in a smoker?
    questionChoices:
    - Anthracotic pigment
    - Melanin pigment
    - Lipofuscin pigment
    - Bilirubin
    correctChoice: Anthracotic pigment
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Cerebral infarction (stroke), most likely results in which of the
      following changes at the tissue level?
    questionChoices:
    - Liquifactive necrosis
    - Coagulative necrosis
    - Caseous necrosis
    - Apoptosis
    correctChoice: Liquifactive necrosis
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 36-year-old woman has been taking aspirin for rheumatoid arthritis.
      Her joint pain is relieved. This pain reduction is most likely to be the result
      of diminishing which of the following chemical mediators?
    questionChoices:
    - Leukotriene B4
    - Interleukin-1
    - Prostaglandin
    - Hageman factor
    correctChoice: Prostaglandin
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The appearance of brush border in certain types of epithelium
      is due to:'
    questionChoices:
    - Presence of desmosomes
    - Presence of microvilli
    - Presence of mucus
    - Presence of cilia
    correctChoice: Presence of microvilli
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'Connexins are found in:'
    questionChoices:
    - Adherens juctions
    - Tight junctions
    - Gap junctions
    - Fascia adherens
    correctChoice: Gap junctions
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'According to secretory mechanisms, sebaceous glands are:'
    questionChoices:
    - Holocrine
    - Paracrine
    - Merocrine
    - Endocrine
    correctChoice: Holocrine
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which cell type gives rise to both memory and effector cells and
      is primarily associated with humoral immunity?
    questionChoices:
    - B lymphocyte
    - Macrophage
    - Reticular cell
    - Natural killer cell
    correctChoice: B lymphocyte
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which structure will express CD8 surface antigen by immunohistochemistry?
    questionChoices:
    - Outer cortex of lymph nodes
    - Bone marrow
    - Paracortex of lymph nodes
    - Splenic cords
    correctChoice: Paracortex of lymph nodes
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Which lymphoid organ normally become less functional with age?
    questionChoices:
    - Splenic white pulp
    - Splenic red pulp
    - Thymus
    - 'Lingual tonsils '
    correctChoice: Thymus
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The tendency for edema to occur will be increased by
    questionChoices:
    - arteriolar constriction
    - increased venous pressure
    - increased plasma protein concentration
    - muscular activity
    correctChoice: increased venous pressure
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  _50pointQ:
  - questionInfo: "A 23-year old man is evaluated for excessive bruising since childhood.
      He says some of his family members \u201Cbleed easily\u201D and sometimes require
      blood transfusions. Temperature is 36.7C\xBA (98.1F). Physical examination
      is unremarkable. Complete blood count is unremarkable. Platelet aggregometry
      is abnormal. Genetic testing identifies a defect in a platelet surface glycoprotein
      receptor that normally binds fibrinogen to support platelet aggregation. The
      abnormal glycoprotein receptor found in this patient is most likely targeted
      by which of the following medication?"
    questionChoices:
    - Abciximab
    - Argatroban
    - Aspirin
    - Clopidogrel
    correctChoice: Abciximab
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'Prolonged QT interval and Buffalo hump appearance are characteristic
      features of:'
    questionChoices:
    - Protease inhibitors
    - Fusion Inhibitors
    - NRTs
    - NNRTs
    correctChoice: Protease inhibitors
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "Which of the following beta blockers is \u03B21 selective and
      has nitric oxide potentiating vasodilatory effects?"
    questionChoices:
    - Esmolol
    - 'Carvedilol '
    - 'Labetalol '
    - Nebivolol
    correctChoice: Nebivolol
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'A 58 year-old woman is being treated for chronic suppression of
      a ventricular arrhythmia. After two months of therapy, she complains about
      feeling tired most of the time. Laboratory tests indicated low thyroxine and
      elevated thyroid-stimulating hormone levels. Which of the following drugs is
      the likely cause:'
    questionChoices:
    - Nifidipine
    - Amiodarone
    - Propranolol
    - Quinidine
    correctChoice: Amiodarone
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'In the Peruvian Andes where the atmospheric pressure is half the
      normal sea level value, the PO2 of tracheal inspired gas is:'
    questionChoices:
    - 60
    - 70
    - 80
    - 90
    correctChoice: 70
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: "Which set of situations describes the elastic property of the
      lung, chest wall & chest-lung system at a volume 500 ml greater than the FRC?
      arrows are used to represent elastic force tending to make the mentioned structure
      expands (\u2191) or collapse (\u2193)."
    questionChoices:
    - A
    - B
    - C
    - D
    correctChoice: D
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: fefa474fc1b85bf439e69c01bead37c4, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: 'Lion-face deformity is characteristic of:'
    questionChoices:
    - Osteopetrosis
    - Osteosarcoma
    - Hyperparathyroidism
    - Paget disease of bone
    correctChoice: Paget disease of bone
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 549296a0b8e76b743a4310ecccd2e020, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: "The disease with ancient description of \u201Cdevil\u2019s bite\u201D
      is characterized by:"
    questionChoices:
    - Bacterial infection
    - Decreased bone mass
    - Crystal deposition
    - Ruptured tendon
    correctChoice: Crystal deposition
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: dcc93afe27fc5094e97798645b54e60c, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: 'Pseudohypertrophy of muscles is seen in a disease with:'
    questionChoices:
    - Trinucleotide repeat
    - X-linked inheritance
    - Benign tumor of adipose tissue
    - Extracellular deposition of fibrillary material
    correctChoice: X-linked inheritance
    questionImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 0562c20a767be1e4396968b0292a3228, type: 3}
  - questionInfo: Which of the following is characteristic for patients with hereditary
      nonpolyposis colorectal cancer syndrome?
    questionChoices:
    - Inherited mutations in TP53 gene.
    - 100% of patients develop colorectal adenocarcinoma by age of 30 if untreated.
    - The most common polyps are hyperplastic polyps.
    - Microsatellite instability is the hallmark of disease.
    correctChoice: Microsatellite instability is the hallmark of disease.
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Patients with Turcot syndrome develop what tumors in addition to
      the typical manifestations of familial adenomatous polyposis?
    questionChoices:
    - Desmoid tumors (fibromatosis)
    - Gastrointestinal stromal tumors
    - Keratoacanthomas
    - Medulloblastomas
    correctChoice: Medulloblastomas
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: An 80 year old gentleman presented with progressive dyspnea of
      5 months duration. On physical examination, he is afebrile. Radiography shows
      a brightly attenuated pleural mass ensheathing most of the right lung. Microscopic
      examination of a pleural biopsy specimen shows atypical spindle and cuboidal
      cells infiltrating adjacent tissue. The condition that this patient mostly
      has is associated with one of the following?
    questionChoices:
    - Horner syndrome
    - Distant metastasis
    - Extensive pleural fibrosis
    - carcinoid syndrome
    correctChoice: Extensive pleural fibrosis
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'regarding the pathogenesis of atopic asthma, one of the following
      statements is CORRECT: '
    questionChoices:
    - 'The initial response upon first exposure is associated with type 1 T helper
      lymphocytes activation '
    - 'IL-4 and IL-5 are released from the alveolar macrophages during the early
      phase response '
    - 'Eotaxin is a potent chemoattractant and activator of eosinophils in late phase '
    - 'Early phase is triggered by Antigen induced cross-linking of IgG bound to
      receptors on mast cells '
    correctChoice: 'Eotaxin is a potent chemoattractant and activator of eosinophils
      in late phase '
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: A 39-year-old woman has had no menstrual periods for the past year,
      along with malaise, cold intolerance, and loss of body hair. She has had headaches
      for the past 5 months. On physical examination her lateral visual fields are
      reduced. She is most likely to have a neoplasm composed of which of the following
      cell types?
    questionChoices:
    - Chromaffin
    - Chromophobe
    - Glomerulosa
    - Parafollicular
    correctChoice: Chromophobe
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'A 28-year-old, otherwise healthy man has had headaches for the
      past 2 weeks. Physical examination yields no remarkable findings except for
      a blood pressure of 174/116 mm Hg. An abdominal CT scan shows an enlarged right
      adrenal gland. A right adrenalectomy is done; the figure shows the gross appearance
      of the specimen. Which of the following laboratory findings in his blood was
      most likely reported in this patient before surgery? '
    questionChoices:
    - Hyponatremia
    - Hyperkalemia
    - Low insulin level
    - Low renin level
    correctChoice: Low renin level
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'A patient with acute myeloid leukemia had recurrent episodes of
      aplastic anemia previously. The most likely pathologic condition is:'
    questionChoices:
    - PIGA gene mutation
    - Mismatch repair defects
    - Telomerase defects
    - Ankyrin gene mutation
    correctChoice: Mismatch repair defects
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: 'The least important test in pre-marital work up for anemia is:'
    questionChoices:
    - Hemoglobin electrophoresis
    - Mean cell volume
    - Serum haptoglobin
    - Blood film
    correctChoice: Serum haptoglobin
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: Pregnant women who have begun labor but in whom this process is
      no longer progressing are often given an IV injection of Pitocin to stimulate
      uterine contractions and facilitate parturition. Pitocin is a trade name of
      a hormone produced in what endocrine tissue?
    questionChoices:
    - Pars distalis
    - Ovarian follicles
    - Pars nervosa
    - Pars tuberalis
    correctChoice: Pars nervosa
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  _10pointQ:
  - questionInfo: Which of the following is a book written by Al-Jahiz
    questionChoices:
    - The beginning and the end
    - Art of war
    - Stingy people
    - Pathoma
    correctChoice: Stingy people
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The largest gulf in the world is
    questionChoices:
    - Gulf of Arabia
    - Gulf of Bengal
    - Gulf of Panama
    - The Gulf Of Mexico
    correctChoice: Gulf of Arabia
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The capital of Portugal is
    questionChoices:
    - Lisbon
    - Benfica
    - Al-Naser
    - Stockholm
    correctChoice: Lisbon
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The gas that makes up 75% of the sun's total mass is
    questionChoices:
    - carbon
    - Nitrogen
    - hydrogen
    - oxygen
    correctChoice: hydrogen
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: His Majesty King Abdullah II assumed his constitutional powers
      in
    questionChoices:
    - 1999
    - 2000
    - 2003
    - 1998
    correctChoice: 1999
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  - questionInfo: The smallest country in the world
    questionChoices:
    - Qatar
    - Al-Bahrain
    - Vatican
    - Kuwait
    correctChoice: Vatican
    questionImage: {fileID: 0}
  quizUIobj: {fileID: 609381636}
  timerObj: {fileID: 1981497918}
